All current categories are closed in the site.

images.caption: Official logo of the feedback site.

texts.text: The Minecraft Feedback Site is the official website location for players to share their feedback for Minecraft. Similar to the bug tracker, the site is moderated by the community team. The feedback site is located here. It currently has 26 categories with which to post feedback in:

Add-ons
Blocks, Tools, and Items
Education Related
Java Combat Snapshot
Minecraft Earth
Java Edition Snapshots
Realms and Dedicated Servers
Sounds
Villagers, NPCs, Humanoids
Bedrock Betas
Commands
Gameplay
Launcher
Minecraft: Dungeons
Mobs, Animals and non-Humanoids
Redstone
Structures
Website
Biomes and Dimensions
Community and Live Events
Graphics
Marketplace/Store
Minecraft (Franchise)
Parity
Scripting and Mods
User Interface, Input Methods and Menu Options
There was a 27th category about what to name the Piglin Beast, announced at MINECON Live 2019. It was decided on the name hoglin, and the category was removed, no longer having a use.
